{
  "page": "Coronation of Rhaenyra Targaryen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaenyra.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a9/Rhaenyra.jpg/300px-Rhaenyra.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"420\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a9/Rhaenyra.jpg/450px-Rhaenyra.jpg 1.5x, /images/a/a9/Rhaenyra.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaenyra.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, by Amok ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>coronation of Rhaenyra Targaryen</b> occurred in <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a> near the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Coronation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Coronation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Royal_House\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Royal House</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Royal_Household\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Royal Household</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Vassals\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vassals</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I Targaryen</a> chose Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, his daughter by his first queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Aemma_Arryn\" title=\"Aemma Arryn\">Aemma Arryn</a>, as his preferred heir over Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, the king's eldest son by his second queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> After Viserys died in his sleep within the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, Alicent concealed the king's death from the public and gathered support in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> for her son, Aegon the Elder, against the claim of Rhaenyra, who was pregnant at <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. Aegon II was soon <a href=\"/index.php/Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Coronation of Aegon II Targaryen\">crowned at the Dragonpit</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Crown#Crown_of_Aegon_I\" title=\"Crown\">the crown</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra</a> learned about the death of her father and the betrayal of her siblings, her anger made her go into labor which lasted for three days and brought forth a stillborn, deformed girl, whom she named <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Visenya</a>. In answer to Aegon's betrayal and the death of her daughter, Rhaenyra swore revenge. She met with her chief supporters, the so-called <a href=\"/index.php/Black_council\" title=\"Black council\">black council</a>, and made plans for her own coronation. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Steffon_Darklyn\" title=\"Steffon Darklyn\">Steffon Darklyn</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, choosing Rhaenyra over Aegon, fled to Dragonstone to give Rhaenyra <a href=\"/index.php/Crown#Crown_of_Jaehaerys_I\" title=\"Crown\">the crown</a> of her father.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Coronation\">Coronation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Coronation\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Rhaenyra was hastily crowned at Dragonstone the day after meeting with her councilors. Three hundred were in attendance as Rhaenyra's husband, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>, placed the crown of King Viserys I and King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> on her head and proclaimed her <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_the_Andals,_the_Rhoynar,_and_the_First_Men\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of the Andals, the Rhoynar, and the First Men\">Queen of the Andals, the Rhoynar, and the First Men</a>. Daemon styled himself <a href=\"/index.php/Protector_of_the_Realm\" title=\"Protector of the Realm\">Protector of the Realm</a>, and Rhaenyra appointed her eldest son, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a>, as <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Prince of Dragonstone\">Prince of Dragonstone</a> and her heir to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Aegon II became outraged after learning of his half sister's coronation, but was convinced to allow Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a> to travel under a peace banner to meet with Rhaenyra. Orwyle's mission was unsuccessful, however, and civil war broke out in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> with the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a> gathered a list of lords who attended Rhaenyra's coronation and sat on her council.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Royal_House\">Royal House</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Royal House\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/20px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/30px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/40px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/20px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/30px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/40px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Lucerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Lucerys Velaryon\">Lucerys Velaryon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/20px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/30px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/40px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Velaryon\" title=\"Joffrey Velaryon\">Joffrey Velaryon</a></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Royal_Household\">Royal Household</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Royal Household\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Erryk_Cargyll\" title=\"Erryk Cargyll\">Erryk Cargyll</a></li>